#: ../../A/angle-brackets.rst:5
msgid "angle brackets"
msgstr "angle brackets"

#: ../../A/angle-brackets.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../A/angle-brackets.rst:9
msgid ""
"Either of the characters ``<`` (ASCII 0111100) and ``>`` (ASCII 0111110) "
"(ASCII less-than or greater-than signs). Typographers in the :ref:`Real-"
"World` use angle brackets which are either taller and slimmer (the ISO lang "
"〈 and rang 〉 characters), or significantly smaller (single or double "
"guillemets) than the less-than and greater-than signs. See :ref:`broket`\\, "
":ref:`ASCII`\\."
msgstr ""
"``<``\\ (ASCII 0111100)と ``>``\\ (ASCII "
"0111110)の各文字(ASCIIの小なり記号・大なり記号)のいずれか。\\ :ref:`Real-World`\\ "
"の組版者は、小なり・大なり記号より背が高く細い山括弧(ISOのlang〈とrang〉の文字)か、あるいは著しく小さい山括弧(単一または二重のギユメ)を使う。\\"
" :ref:`broket`\\ 、\\ :ref:`ASCII`\\ を参照。"
